@startuml
title Giant 2048 Current Protocol Flow

actor Player
participant "Frontend\nGameScene + Sling" as FE
participant "ActionRecorder" as Recorder
participant "Workers API" as API
database "D1 DB" as DB

== Start Game ==
Player -> FE: Enter game
FE -> Recorder: init(userId)
Recorder -> API: POST /api/start-game\n{ fingerprint, userId }
API -> DB: close old playing games for fingerprint
API -> DB: select random enabled generated_sequence\nor generate one from sequence_plan
API -> DB: insert games row\n(status=playing, sign=initSign, sequence_plan_id,\ngenerated_sequence_id)
API --> Recorder: { gameId, sequence, sequencePlanId,\ngeneratedSequenceId, sign }

Recorder -> Recorder: consume sequence tokens locally
note right of Recorder
  sequence is the only content source
  numeric string => candy
  "stone" => spawn obstacle instruction
end note

Recorder --> FE: prepareInitialCandies()\n=> currentCandy + nextCandy
FE -> FE: if token == "stone"\nspawnStone()
FE -> FE: Sling.initCandies(currentCandy, nextCandy)

== During Gameplay ==
Player -> FE: shoot / rotate / direct merge
FE -> Recorder: recordShoot / recordRotate /\nrecordDirectMerge
Recorder -> API: POST /api/action\n{ gameId, action }
API -> DB: update games.step, games.sign,\ngames.last_update_at
API --> Recorder: { step, sign }
Recorder -> Recorder: currentSign = sign

FE -> Recorder: reportScore(score)
Recorder -> API: POST /api/update-score\n{ gameId, score }
API -> DB: update games.score,\ngames.last_update_at
API --> Recorder: { success: true }

FE -> Recorder: advanceAfterShot()
Recorder -> Recorder: keep consuming local sequence
Recorder --> FE: { currentCandy, nextCandy }
FE -> FE: if token == "stone"\nspawnStone()
FE -> FE: update sling current/preview

== End Game ==
FE -> Recorder: finish(finalScore, endReason)
Recorder -> API: POST /api/end-game\n{ gameId, finalSign, finalScore, endReason }
API -> DB: verify finalSign == games.sign
API -> DB: update games\n(score, status=finished, end_reason,\nended_at, last_update_at)
API -> DB: insert scores row
API --> Recorder: { success, score, rank }
Recorder --> FE: { rank }

== Compatibility Alias ==
note over API
  /api/submit-game is currently a compatibility alias
  of /api/end-game and accepts the same payload:
  { gameId, finalSign, finalScore, endReason }
end note

@enduml
